The paper deals with the analysis of co-authorship networks and proposes a method for detecting densely knit communities of researchers. This falls under the scope of social network analysis (SNA) and community detection, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with SNA and community detection. cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a method for organizing personal academic networks, which could be relevant to software engineering research. cs.SNA (Social Network and Graph Analysis) is another possible category as it deals with the analysis of social networks. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.DB (Databases) are also possible categories as the paper deals with bibliographic information and co-authorship data.
